Our Staff

Meet Our doctors and staff

Our medical staff is highly trained and educated to provide the best care for your child. Keep your child on the right track for a healthy childhood with services from our wonderful staff. All our pediatricians are board-certified and are members of the American Academy of PediatricsÂ®. From newborn visits and immunizations to school and sports physicals, acute care, illness treatments, our professional team is committed to serving your young ones' health care needs.


Every child deserves the best possible medical care. At Honeygo Pediatrics, our team of caregivers partners with parents to help raise healthy children, both physically and emotionally. Each member of our team is dedicated to the health and well-being of our patients. We strive to provide quality, compassionate care in a warm, friendly environment.

Wieslawa D. Wisinski, MD

Board Certified Pediatric and Adolescent Specialty

Dr. Wieslawa D. Wisinski, M.D. is a Board Certified Pediatrician, a physician specializing in serving medical care for children of all ages.

With over 30 years of exerience as a pediatrician, she offers extensive healthcare for babies, kids, and teenagers in the greater White Marsh, Perry Hall, Towson, Baltimore area, and beyond.

Dr. Wisinski earned her medical degree from Jagiellonian University Medical School, Poland. She completed her internship and pediatric residency at the University of Maryland.

After her residency, Dr. Wisinski worked for several years as a peditrician at Johns Hopkins Bayview ER. She later joined Med Star Pediatrics at White Marsh and now, for more than 20 years, she serves her pediatric patients at Honeygo Pediatrics in White Marsh.

She is certified by the American Board of Pediatrics.

Languages spoken: English and Polish.

Christina Green, CRNP

Board Certified Registered Nurse Practitioner

Dr. Christina Green graduated in 2004 from Stevenson University with a Bachelor of Science in Nursing.

In 2011, she graduated from the University of Maryland School of Nursing and Pediatric Nurse Practitioner's program, earning her masters degree.

She has been a Pediatric Nurse Practitioner (PNP) at Honeygo Pediatrics since 2013.

She is certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners (AANP).

Stephanie Skrobiszewski, FNP

Board Certified Family Nurse Practitioner

Dr. Stephanie Skrobiszewski received her Bachelor of Science in Nursing in 2015 from Wilkes Barre University, located in Wilkes Barre, Pennsylvania.

In 2021, she graduated from Drexel University located in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, where she received a Master of Science and Nursing under the Family Nurse Practitioner program.

She has been a Family Nurse Practitioner at Honeygo Pediatrics since 2021.

She is certified by the American Academy of Nurse Practitioners (AANP).
